snippet: The company had until Thursday night to submit the proposals to end a three-year investigation focused on the dominance of its search service.
abstract: European officials say that Google has submitted proposals aimed at ending a three-year antitrust case focused on its search service, but the offer does not prevent rivals from seeking to prolong its legal problems.

byline.contributor: Claire Cain Miller contributed reporting from San Francisco.

lead_paragraph: The company had until Thursday night to submit the proposals to end a three-year investigation focused on the dominance of its search service.

headline.main: Google Makes Offer in 3-Year European Antitrust Case
headline.print_headline: Google Makes Offer in 3-Year European Antitrust Case
